However, Tottenham have moved quickly to hijack the deal.

Montpellier released a statement on their website that read: 'An agreement has been reached between Montpellier and Tottenham to transfer Benjamin Stambouli.'

'He will go to London in the next few hours to undergo a medical and finalise his contract.' 

Stambouli is known for his versatility and played as a defensive midfielder, centre back and full back for Montpellier last season.  

